Actually, I realize there's an even simpler approach. I can just format the digits as a string and then insert 
the decimal point at the right position.

```rust
fn fmt_decimal(digits_str: &str, scale: usize) -> String {
    if scale == 0 {
        return digits_str.to_string();
    }
    if digits_str.len() <= scale {
        format!("0.{}{}", "0".repeat(scale - digits_str.len()), digits_str)
    } else {
        let pos = digits_str.len() - scale;
        format!("{}.{})", &digits_str[..pos], &digits_str[pos..])
    }
}
```

